Outcome Informed Analysis¶

This analysis is done after peeking at the learning outcomes.

Outcomes:

  • Develop students’ globalized perspectives in their learning
  • Promote understanding through interdisciplinary lenses with which to examine pertinent world issues
  • Develop cultural awareness, interculturality, growth required for communication (scientific and otherwise) and engagement

Discussion 1: Consider the impact of the global COVID pandemic on learning and education in general.

  • Identifying similarities and differences encountered in Iraq and US relating to the pandemic's impact on education and learning, and considered any cultural, discipline, and language factors that might have played a role.
  • Developing understanding from the group's discussion that contributed to any aspect of their cultural understanding and growth.

Discussion 2: Consider issues that present as gender-related inequities or challenges facing individuals pursuing their education and/or career/professional development.

  • Identifying commonalities/differences relating to these gender issues and the factors that contribute to them, comparing across US and Iraq contexts (specifically, cultural, discipline/field of study, and language factors that might play a role in promoting/reducing gender-related inequities or challenges to education and career opportunities).
  • Developing understanding from the group's discussion that contributed to any aspect of their cultural understanding and growth.

Discussion 3: Critically reflect on the advantages and/or disadvantages of having 'English-only' as the language of communication (both verbal and written) in this COIL experience and any other academic initiatives.

  • Developing understanding from the group's discussion and what contributed to language awareness and intercultural understanding (specifically issues related to the use of English as a lingua franca, and as a communication tool for speakers of diverse linguacultural backgrounds).
  • Developing awareness of any issues of misunderstanding and communication difficulties related to English practice experienced in from their COIL participation.

# saving
import re
for word in words:
    with open('searches/' + word + '-iq-gender.txt', 'w') as f:
        for tup in set(find_word_in_sentences(word, sent[(sent['TOPIC'] == 'gender') & (sent['STATE'] == 'iq')])):
            f.write('Topic : ' + tup[0]); f.write('\n')
            f.write('State : ' + tup[1]); f.write('\n')
            f.write('DocID : ' + str(tup[2])); f.write('\n')
            f.write('Text : ' + re.sub(r'\.', '.\n', tup[5])); f.write('\n')
            f.write('\n')
    with open('searches/' + word + '-us-gender.txt', 'w') as f:
        for tup in set(find_word_in_sentences(word, sent[(sent['TOPIC'] == 'gender') & (sent['STATE'] == 'us')])):
